  <data name="ComicSourcesHelpExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Comic Sources</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ComicSourcesHelpExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Understanding Yukari plugins</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ComicSourcesHelp1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>**Yukari** doesn't come with pre-installed **Comic Sources** for legal reasons. You add the sources you want through **community plugins**.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ComicSourcesHelp2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Installing a **Comic Source** is simple: download the **.dll** plugin, go to: **Settings → Comic Sources → Add New Source** and select the downloaded plugin.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ComicSourcesHelp3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You can find the plugins [HERE](https://github.com/orgs/Yukari-App/repositories?q=Plugin%20sort%3Aname-asc). Select a **repository** with "Plugin" in the name, go to the **releases** section, and download a compatible version.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ComicSourcesHelp4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>**Make sure you are using the latest version of Yukari** to guarantee compatibility with the newest plugins. Check the [releases page](https://github.com/Yukari-App/Yukari/releases).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ComicsSection.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Comics</value>
  </data>
  <data name="OnlineComicsHelpExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Online</value>
  </data>
  <data name="OnlineComicsHelpExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Discovering and reading comics from plugins</value>
  </data>
  <data name="OnlineComicsHelp1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Use the **Discover** page to browse trending comics or search by title across your installed sources.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="OnlineComicsHelp2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Favoriting a comic saves it to your library and enables **Downloads** feature per chapter and language.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="OnlineComicsHelp3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Chapters are **not updated automatically**. Use the **Update** option in the Comic page menu to fetch new chapters.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="LocalComicsHelpExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Local</value>
  </data>
  <data name="LocalComicsHelpExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Reading your personal comic collection</value>
  </data>
  <data name="LocalComicsHelp1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Yukari supports two local formats: **folders containing images** (one folder per chapter) and **.cbz** archives. Pages are read directly without extraction.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="LocalComicsHelp2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>To add a local comic: open **Favorites** → ⋯ menu → **Add Local Comic**. Fill in the details and point to the folder containing your chapters.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="LocalComicsHelp3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>If you add new chapters to the folder, use **Rescan Chapters** on the Comic page to detect them. Removing a local comic from favorites **never deletes your original files**.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ReaderHelpExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Reader</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ReaderHelpExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Reading modes, scaling and shortcuts</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ReaderHelp1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Three reading modes are available: **Right to Left** (manga), **Left to Right**, (western) and **Vertical** (webtoons). Change via the reader menu.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ReaderHelp2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Four scaling modes: **Fit Screen**, **Fit Width**, **Fit Height** and **Original Size**. Press **F11** or use **Fullscreen** button to toggle fullscreen.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ReaderHelp3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The **Continue** button on the Comic page resumes from your last read chapter and page automatically.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="PersistenceSection.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Persistence</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DownloadsHelpExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Downloads</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DownloadsHelpExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Offline reading and storage management</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DownloadsHelp1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Download chapters from the Comic page to read them **offline**. Downloads run in the background and progress is shown per chapter.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DownloadsHelp2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Downloaded chapters are stored in **Yukari's app data folder**. You can delete individual chapters or all at once from the Comic page.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DownloadsHelp3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Removing a comic from favorites **automatically deletes all its downloaded data**.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SupportSection.Text" xml:space="preserve">
